---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="ICF Construction Ontario | ICF Homes & Basements | PCM Homes" description="ICF construction specialists in Ontario. Build stronger, more energy-efficient homes with Insulated Concrete Forms. ICF basements, full homes, and cottages. 50-70% energy savings.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section data-hero="dark" class="relative min-h-[70vh] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="/images/projects/image00004.jpeg"
        alt="ICF home construction by PCM Homes in Ontario"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-black/60 via-black/50 to-black/70"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 text-center text-white pt-24">
      <p class="section-label text-white/80 mb-4">Build Stronger</p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-display font-medium mb-6">
        ICF <span class="italic">Construction</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-white/80 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        Insulated Concrete Forms create homes that are stronger, quieter, and 50-70% more energy efficient than traditional construction.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">
          <span>Get ICF Quote</span>
        </a>
        <a href="tel:9057161939" class="btn-secondary border-white text-white hover:bg-white hover:text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">
          Call (905) 716-1939
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What is ICF Section -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-cream)]">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">The Basics</p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
        What is <span class="italic">ICF Construction?</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="divider mb-10"></div>

      <!-- Featured Snippet Target -->
      <div class="bg-white p-8 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-timber)] mb-10">
        <p class="text-xl font-medium text-[var(--color-charcoal)] leading-relaxed">
          ICF (Insulated Concrete Forms) construction uses interlocking foam blocks that stack like Lego, get filled with reinforced concrete, and stay in place as permanent insulation. The result: walls that are 6-9x stronger than wood frame, with built-in R-22+ insulation and no thermal bridging.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-pcm text-lg">
        <p class="mb-6">
          Traditional concrete forms get stripped away after the pour. ICF forms stay put. The EPS foam on both sides of the concrete core provides continuous insulation from foundation to roof. No studs conducting heat through your wall assembly. No gaps or voids.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          We've been building with ICF for 9 years. Started with basements, then moved to full above-grade walls. The learning curve is realâ€”ICF requires different techniques than wood framing. But the results speak for themselves: clients who build ICF come back years later to tell us their heating bills are half what their neighbors pay.
        </p>
        <p>
          ICF works for basements only, full homes, or anything in between. Most of our clients start with an ICF basement and traditional framing above. Some go all-in. We'll help you figure out what makes sense for your project and budget.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How ICF Works -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">The Process</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          How ICF <span class="italic">Works</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-20 h-20 mx-auto mb-6 bg-[var(--color-cream)] flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-3xl font-display text-[var(--color-timber)]">01</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Stack the Forms</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Foam blocks interlock and stack dry. Cut openings for windows and doors. Brace the walls plumb.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-20 h-20 mx-auto mb-6 bg-[var(--color-cream)] flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-3xl font-display text-[var(--color-timber)]">02</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Install Rebar</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Horizontal and vertical rebar goes inside the foam cavity. This creates a reinforced concrete core.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-20 h-20 mx-auto mb-6 bg-[var(--color-cream)] flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-3xl font-display text-[var(--color-timber)]">03</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Pour Concrete</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Pump concrete into the cavity. Work in lifts to prevent blowouts. Vibrate to consolidate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="w-20 h-20 mx-auto mb-6 bg-[var(--color-cream)] flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-3xl font-display text-[var(--color-timber)]">04</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Finish</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Foam stays as insulation. Attach drywall inside, siding outside directly to embedded strips.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ICF vs Traditional Comparison -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-cream)] grain-overlay">
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">Comparison</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          ICF vs <span class="italic">Wood Frame</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white overflow-hidden">
        <table class="w-full">
          <thead class="bg-[var(--color-charcoal)] text-white">
            <tr>
              <th class="text-left p-6 font-display text-lg">Feature</th>
              <th class="text-center p-6 font-display text-lg">ICF</th>
              <th class="text-center p-6 font-display text-lg">Wood Frame</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-[var(--color-stone)]/20">
            <tr>
              <td class="p-6 text-[var(--color-charcoal)] font-medium">Wall R-Value</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">R-22 to R-26</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-slate)]">R-19 (nominal)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[var(--color-cream)]/50">
              <td class="p-6 text-[var(--color-charcoal)] font-medium">Thermal Bridging</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">None</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-slate)]">25% wall area</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-6 text-[var(--color-charcoal)] font-medium">Energy Savings</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">50-70%</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-slate)]">Baseline</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[var(--color-cream)]/50">
              <td class="p-6 text-[var(--color-charcoal)] font-medium">Structural Strength</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">6-9x stronger</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-slate)]">Baseline</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-6 text-[var(--color-charcoal)] font-medium">Sound Rating (STC)</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">50+</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-slate)]">35-40</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[var(--color-cream)]/50">
              <td class="p-6 text-[var(--color-charcoal)] font-medium">Fire Rating</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">4 hours</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-slate)]">1 hour</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-6 text-[var(--color-charcoal)] font-medium">Lifespan</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">100+ years</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-slate)]">50-80 years</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-[var(--color-cream)]/50">
              <td class="p-6 text-[var(--color-charcoal)] font-medium">Upfront Cost</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-slate)]">5-10% higher</td>
              <td class="p-6 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">Lower</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Benefits Grid -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">Why ICF</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          Benefits of <span class="italic">ICF Construction</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">50-70% Energy Savings</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Continuous insulation eliminates thermal bridging. Concrete thermal mass stabilizes indoor temperatures. Your furnace and AC run half as much.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Disaster Resistant</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">6-9x stronger than wood frame. ICF walls withstand 250 mph winds, resist earthquake damage, and won't burn. Built to last generations.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M4.318 6.318a4.5 4.5 0 000 6.364L12 20.364l7.682-7.682a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364-6.364L12 7.636l-1.318-1.318a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Year-Round Comfort</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Thermal mass eliminates temperature swings. No cold spots near walls in winter or hot rooms in summer. Every room stays comfortable.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M15.536 8.464a5 5 0 010 7.072m2.828-9.9a9 9 0 010 12.728M5.586 15H4a1 1 0 01-1-1v-4a1 1 0 011-1h1.586l4.707-4.707C10.923 3.663 12 4.109 12 5v14c0 .891-1.077 1.337-1.707.707L5.586 15z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Superior Soundproofing</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">With an STC rating of 50+, ICF walls block traffic noise, barking dogs, and loud neighbors. Inside stays quiet regardless of what's happening outside.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">100+ Year Lifespan</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Concrete doesn't rot, rust, or degrade like wood. ICF structures maintain their integrity for generations. This is a home you can pass down.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Higher Resale Value</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Energy-efficient, disaster-resistant homes command premium prices. Buyers recognize ICF quality. Insurance companies often offer discounts too.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ICF Applications -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-cream)]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">Applications</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          Where ICF <span class="italic">Works Best</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="group">
          <div class="img-zoom mb-6">
            <img
              src="/images/projects/image00006.jpeg"
              alt="ICF basement construction"
              class="w-full aspect-[4/3] object-cover"
            />
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">ICF Basements</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The most popular ICF application in Ontario. ICF basement walls resist water infiltration, eliminate cold concrete walls, and create livable space from day one. No need for framing and insulating later.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-stone)] text-sm italic">
            Best for: Any new home wanting a warm, dry, usable basement
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="group">
          <div class="img-zoom mb-6">
            <img
              src="/images/projects/image00004.jpeg"
              alt="Full ICF home construction"
              class="w-full aspect-[4/3] object-cover"
            />
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Full ICF Homes</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Basement to roof in ICF creates the ultimate energy-efficient home. These structures meet or exceed Passive House standards without special engineering. Ideal for those building their forever home.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-stone)] text-sm italic">
            Best for: Custom builds prioritizing long-term value and efficiency
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="group">
          <div class="img-zoom mb-6">
            <img
              src="/images/projects/image00011.jpeg"
              alt="ICF cottage in Muskoka"
              class="w-full aspect-[4/3] object-cover"
            />
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">ICF Cottages</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Muskoka and Kawartha cottage country gets harsh winters. ICF cottages stay warm with minimal heating, resist tree-fall damage, and require less maintenance than wood construction in damp environments.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-stone)] text-sm italic">
            Best for: Waterfront properties and remote locations
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cost Section -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">Investment</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          ICF Construction <span class="italic">Costs</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center mb-8"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-pcm max-w-none">
        <p class="text-lg">
          Let's talk real numbers. ICF construction costs more upfront than traditional wood frame. Pretending otherwise does you no favors.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mt-8 mb-4">Typical Cost Differences</h3>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>ICF Basement Only:</strong> Add $15,000-$30,000 compared to poured concrete with later framing and insulation. However, you skip the future basement finishing cost.</li>
          <li><strong>Full ICF Walls:</strong> 5-10% higher than wood frame for the wall assembly. On a $500,000 build, that's $25,000-$50,000 more.</li>
          <li><strong>Complete ICF Home:</strong> Premium of 8-12% over comparable wood-frame construction when including all factors.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mt-8 mb-4">The Payback Math</h3>

        <p>
          Ontario heating and cooling costs average $2,400-$3,600 per year for a typical home. ICF cuts that by 50-70%.
        </p>
        <p>
          Annual savings: $1,200-$2,500<br />
          Payback period: 5-10 years<br />
          Lifetime savings (30 years): $36,000-$75,000
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mt-8 mb-4">What Drives ICF Costs</h3>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Project size:</strong> Larger projects have better economies of scale</li>
          <li><strong>Wall complexity:</strong> Straight walls cost less than complex angles</li>
          <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Remote sites increase concrete delivery costs</li>
          <li><strong>ICF brand:</strong> Premium brands cost more but install faster</li>
          <li><strong>Contractor experience:</strong> Experienced ICF crews work faster and waste less</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-8 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-timber)] mt-8">
          <p class="text-[var(--color-charcoal)] font-medium mb-2">Our recommendation:</p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)]">
            If you're building a home you plan to keep for 10+ years, ICF makes financial sense. If you're building to flip or holding less than 5 years, stick with wood frame. We'll help you run the numbers for your specific project.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our ICF Process -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-charcoal)]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label text-[var(--color-timber)] mb-4">Our Approach</p>
          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-white mb-8">
            PCM's ICF <span class="italic">Process</span>
          </h2>
          <div class="w-16 h-px bg-[var(--color-timber)] mb-8"></div>

          <div class="space-y-6 text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              We've handled ICF projects from start to finish for 9 years. Our crew does both ICF and wood framing in-house, which means we control quality and scheduling without relying on subcontractor availability.
            </p>
            <p>
              Every ICF project starts with a detailed scope review. We walk through the plans, identify potential issues, and give you a fixed price before any work begins. No surprises.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-8">
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-white font-medium mb-3">What We Handle</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-white/60">
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-[var(--color-timber)]"></div>
                  ICF foundation walls
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-[var(--color-timber)]"></div>
                  Above-grade ICF walls
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-[var(--color-timber)]"></div>
                  Concrete pour coordination
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-[var(--color-timber)]"></div>
                  Window/door integration
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-white font-medium mb-3">Communication</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-white/60">
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-[var(--color-timber)]"></div>
                  Weekly photo updates
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-[var(--color-timber)]"></div>
                  Direct owner access
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-[var(--color-timber)]"></div>
                  Same-day responses
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-[var(--color-timber)]"></div>
                  Clear milestone tracking
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

