            <p>Standard ICF walls provide R-22 to R-26 depending on the foam thickness and brand. More importantly, that R-value is continuous with no thermal bridging. A wood-frame wall rated R-19 actually performs closer to R-14 in real conditions because studs conduct heat. ICF's R-22 performs like R-22.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-6">
